            "answer_text": "Let common factor of ratio of angles is X. Ratios are 2:3:5 given. So, 2*X+3*X+5*x=180\u00b0 \u2014 sum of three angles of a triangle. Now, 10*X=180\u00b0 So, X=18\u00b0. Hence angles are 36\u00b0 , 54\u00b0 and 90\u00b0. ",
